original: Dellborg, Carl Dani&l Evald, hamn-direktör, Göteborg, f. 3/10/03 i Göteborg. G. 32 m. Barbro Lundström. Barn: Berit f. 38, Helen 43. — Stud ex. v. Gbgs real 23, avg:ex. fr. CTH (V) 28. Bitr. ing. v. Gbgs hamnstyr. 28-30, e. byråing. 30-32, tf. arb :chef 32-35, arb xhef 35-44, konstr:chef 44-47, hamndir. fr. 47. Kassör i Chailmers ing:fören. 33-38, led. av Tekn. samf. i Gbg 28, sekr. i avd. väig o. vatten 36-38, led. av Sv. tekn:fören. ’Sed. 31.
translated: Dellborg, Carl Dani&l Evald, port director, Gothenburg, born October 3rd, 1903 in Gothenburg. Married in 1932 to Barbro Lundström. Children: Berit, born 1938, Helen, born 1943. He completed his studies at Gothenburg's Real School in 1923 and graduated with a degree from Chalmers University of Technology in 1928. He worked as an assistant engineer for Gothenburg's Port Authority from 1928-1930, then as a bureau engineer from 1930-1932, acting as a chief executive from 1932-1935, an executive chief from 1935-1944, a construction chief from 1944-1947, and as port director from 1947. He was treasurer of the Chalmers Engineering Society from 1933-1938, a member of the Technical Society in Gothenburg in 1928, secretary of the Road and Water Division from 1936-1938, and a member of the Swedish Engineering Association since 1931.
